            <p class="text-justify">
                "Pung cholom" literally means "roar of the drums". It is the soul of Manipuri Sankir. It is showcased and highly acclaimed all over the globe as part of the Manipuri Classical music and dance with high acrobatic skills needed to perform this dance form. The dance form is known for its rhythmic beats and the coordination between the dancers and the musicians. The dance involves devotion which is shown in the beat of drums and high skill performed by the dancer. 
                This dance form is performed in the spring season during Yaosang Festival and also in other traditional events.
            </p>
